    The `TokenRelay` filter copies the bearer token from the incoming request and adds it to the outgoing request to downstream services. 
    Each downstream service can then do its own JWT validation with its own `SecurityFilterChain`.

Putting It All Together — the Complete Mental Model

    The full flow from browser to database looks like this:
    Browser / Mobile client
        ↓  POST /api/auth/login  {username, password}
    API Gateway (Spring Cloud Gateway)
        ↓  forwards to auth service
    Auth Service
        ↓  AuthenticationManager → DaoAuthenticationProvider
        ↓  UserDetailsService loads user → PasswordEncoder verifies
        ↓  JwtTokenService signs JWT with RSA private key from server keystore
        ↑  returns {token: "eyJ..."}
    
    --- subsequent request ---
    
    Browser
        ↓  GET /api/orders  Authorization: Bearer eyJ...
    API Gateway
        ↓  JwtDecoder validates signature against public key (or JWKS endpoint)
        ↓  TokenRelay forwards JWT
    Order Service (Spring Boot)
        ↓  BearerTokenAuthenticationFilter extracts token
        ↓  JwtAuthenticationProvider validates again (defense in depth)
        ↓  SecurityContextHolder holds JwtAuthenticationToken
        ↓  AuthorizationFilter checks @PreAuthorize("hasRole('USER')")
        ↓  OrderController.getOrders(@AuthenticationPrincipal Jwt jwt)

