Secret Rotation & Refresh:
    Secret = the key used to SIGN and VERIFY JWT tokens
    WITHOUT rotation:                    WITH rotation:
    ──────────────────                   ─────────────────
    One secret forever                   Secret changes periodically
    If leaked → ALL tokens               If leaked → only tokens from
    compromised forever 😱               that period are affected ✅
    
    secret = "mySecret123"               secret_v1 = "secret_jan_2026" (expired)
                                         secret_v2 = "secret_feb_2026" (expired)
                                         secret_v3 = "secret_mar_2026" (current)
Reasons to rotate:
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  1. Employee leaves   → revoke their access             │
│  2. Secret leaked     → limit blast radius              │
│  3. Compliance        → PCI-DSS, SOC2 require rotation  │
│  4. Scheduled policy  → rotate every 30/60/90 days      │
│  5. Suspected breach  → emergency rotation              │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
JWT Token Lifecycle
                    ACCESS TOKEN (short-lived)
                    ┌────────────────────────┐
                    │  expires: 15 mins      │
User logs in ──►    │  carries: roles,email  │──► used for API calls
                    │  signed: with secret   │
                    └────────────────────────┘
                               +
                    REFRESH TOKEN (long-lived)
                    ┌────────────────────────┐
                    │  expires: 7–30 days    │
                    │  stored: in DB/Redis   │──► used ONLY to get new access token
                    │  one-time use (ideally)│
                    └────────────────────────┘

Flow:
    1. Login           → get Access Token (15min) + Refresh Token (7days)
    2. API calls       → use Access Token
    3. Access expires  → use Refresh Token to get NEW Access Token
    4. Refresh expires → force re-login

