 When to Use What
Use Apigee when:
✅ You are a large enterprise
✅ You sell APIs to external partners/developers
✅ You need monetization (charge per API call)
✅ You need a developer portal
✅ You need advanced analytics & SLA reporting
✅ You have a dedicated API team
Example: Bank exposing APIs to fintech partners

Use AWS/Azure API Gateway when:
✅ Already on that cloud provider
✅ Serverless architecture (Lambda functions)
✅ Want managed service with minimal ops
Example: Startup on AWS with Lambda backends

Use Spring Cloud Gateway when:
✅ All services are Spring Boot
✅ Want full code control
✅ Self-hosted microservices
✅ No budget for commercial gateway
Example: In-house microservices platform

Use Resource Server (Spring Security) when:
✅ ALWAYS — every service needs this
✅ Fine-grained role/permission checks
✅ Business logic security (@PreAuthorize)
✅ Works behind any gateway
Example: Every microservice in your system

## Key Takeaway
They are NOT alternatives — they work TOGETHER:
Apigee/Gateway  =  Security + Traffic layer    (macro level)
Resource Server =  Business security layer     (micro level)
Auth Server     =  Identity layer              (token issuer)

